28299.title: Premiere Promenade
28299.credit_line: The Robert and Traude Hensel Collection
28299.medium_support: pen, ink and watercolor on off-white paper
28299.inscription: signed and dated in ink, L.R.: Man Ray - 12

extended_text.content:
The strangely distorted imagery creates a whimsical effect based on fantasy rather than reality.

Later in his career Man Ray was considered a member of the Dada and Surrealist Movements, which contained strikingly incongruous juxtapositions of images similar to this work.
extended_text.title: Gallery Label

28299.exhibit_history: A Century of American Watercolors, Center for the Arts, Vero Beach, Florida, 09/01/2001-11/11/2001|
